<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Additional Information</h1>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Mission Goal</h2>
            <p>
                At Cana House, we are committed to fostering a spirit of inclusivity, love, and service in the heart of our community. As a Catholic hospitality house, our mission is to provide a safe
                and welcoming space where individuals of all backgrounds can come together in fellowship. We believe in nurturing both spiritual and personal growth through our various programs, which
                include shared meals, special events, and community-building activities.
            <p></p>
            What We Offer:
            <p></p>
            Inclusive Dinners: Free, open-to-all dinners that provide nourishment for both the body and soul.
            <p></p>
            Engaging Events: A variety of activities, from faith-based reflections to fun, social gatherings, designed to strengthen our community ties.
            Volunteering Opportunities: We offer ways for individuals to give back through service to others, reflecting the true spirit of hospitality.
            Clubs & Social Groups: Join our Benedictine Club and other groups for deeper engagement, spiritual reflection, and fellowship.
            Support Our Mission: Opportunities to donate and support our ongoing efforts to expand our outreach and programs for the community. Your contributions help us continue our mission
            of love and service to all.
            We invite you to become part of our vibrant community—whether through participation in our activities, serving others, or supporting us financially—as we build a brighter, more connected
            future together.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h3>Important Information</h3>
            <p><strong>Meeting Place:</strong> Basement of St Joseph’s Church (801 Spring Garden)</p>
            <p><strong>Available Dates:</strong> October 20, Nov 17, Dec 25 (3pm - 5pm)</p>
            <p><strong>Meeting Times:</strong> 12pm - 2pm, Every third Sunday</p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section" style="display: flex; align-items: center;">
            <div style="flex: 1; margin-right: 20px;">
                <img src="/images/Sienkiewitcz.JPG" style="max-width: 300px; height: auto; border-radius: 8px;">
            </div>
            <div style="flex: 2;">
                <h3>Director of Cana House of Hospitality</h3>
                <p><strong>Dr. Sienkiewicz</strong></p>
                <p>
                    Dr. Jeremy Sienkiewicz, a native of Kansas City, Missouri, graduated with a B.A. from the University of Notre Dame and received an M.A. and Ph.D. in Systematic Theology
                    from The Catholic University of America. He teaches classes in missiology, sacramental theology, and spiritual theology at Benedictine College. In his own time, he enjoys powerlifting, reading
                    classic books to his children, and baking bread. He, his wife, Catherine, and his five children live in Atchison, Kansas.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

